parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, making it difficult or impossible to turn off the engine, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key refuses to turn back into the off position
the key becomes locked in the ignition
the vehicle will not shut off
the key will not release from the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various gauges to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings, and can also cause the vehicle to shut off unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The radio produces an extremely loud screeching sound
the dash and brake lights produce an electrical crackling sound
the airbag light flashes off and on
the AWD light is on all the time
the gas gauge always reads below "E"
gauges do not work properly
the speedometer acts up
the battery light illuminates
the vehicle loses power at various speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The temperature gauge shoots up to hot
the radiator hoses burst due to pressure buildup
the vehicle shuts off
and the temperature light blinks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system issues can cause a strong fuel odor, which can be a fire hazard, and erratic fuel level indicators, which can lead to unexpected stalling, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor inside and outside the vehicle
especially in cold weather
fuel odor stronger when the vehicle is not moving
erratic fuel level indicators
fuel gauge not working properly
fuel gauge showing empty or past empty
stalling when driving downhill.

symptoms: Erratic fuel level indicators
fuel gauge not working properly
fuel gauge showing empty or past empty
stalling when driving downhill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hard shifting between gears can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
